{% from "source-toggle.njk" import autoToggle %}
<h2>Background Task Surface</h2>
<p>
    The persistent app-shell surface that hosts long-running work <strong>after it goes async</strong> &mdash;
    the receiving end of a <a href="/intents/loader/">Loader</a>'s <code>escalation: async</code> handoff.
    It implements the <a href="/intents/background-task/">Background Task Intent</a>: the intent declares
    <em>what</em> should be true of that surface; this block is the surface itself.
</p>
<p>
    It renders one entry per registered task with per-task progress, exposes per-task retry, and arms the
    navigation-away guard while any task is in flight. It is a distinct UX surface, not a loader: it
    <strong>outlives the originating view</strong> and aggregates concurrent tasks.
</p>

<h3>Not the Loader, not Feedback</h3>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr><th></th><th><a href="/intents/loader/">Loader</a></th><th>Background Task Surface</th><th><a href="/intents/feedback/">Feedback</a></th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Lifetime</strong></td>
            <td>Dies with its view</td>
            <td>Outlives the originating view</td>
            <td>Transient, fire-and-forget</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Tracks ongoing state</strong></td>
            <td>Yes (in-view)</td>
            <td>Yes (off-view, aggregated)</td>
            <td>No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Concurrency</strong></td>
            <td>One pending region</td>
            <td>Many tasks, per-task progress + retry</td>
            <td>A queue of notices</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Relationship</strong></td>
            <td>Upstream (hands a task here at <code>escalation: async</code>)</td>
            <td>&mdash;</td>
            <td>Downstream (may emit a toast on completion)</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Composition (defers, does not redefine)</h3>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr><th>Intent</th><th>What this surface borrows</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="/intents/loader/">Loader</a></td>
            <td>Per-task progress is the Loader's <code>determinate</code>/<code>indeterminate</code> indicator, version/generation token, and lifecycle &mdash; the same state machine, hosted off-view. The handoff transfers a live handle, not a snapshot.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="/intents/reliability/">Reliability</a></td>
            <td>Retry of a failed task delegates here; the surface exposes only the affordance, not the recovery policy.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="/intents/layout/">Layout</a></td>
            <td>The surface is an app-shell region &mdash; a persistent <code>rail</code> (Layout's edge-region behavior). Placement mechanics defer to Layout.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="/intents/feedback/">Feedback</a></td>
            <td>Downstream. A completed task may emit a transient toast (<code>withCompletionToast</code>); Feedback does not track ongoing state, this surface does.</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Web Standards Alignment</h3>
<table>
    <tr><th>Standard</th><th>Status</th><th>How We Adopt It</th></tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/CustomEvent">CustomEvent</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td>Registration is a bubbling <code>background-task-register</code> event carrying the Loader-state handle &mdash; a one-shot handoff that decouples the surface from the (possibly torn-down) originating element.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/beforeunload_event">beforeunload</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td>The cross-document half of <code>navigationGuard: warn</code> &mdash; arms while any task is active, cleared when the last resolves.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigation/navigate_event">Navigation API <code>navigate</code></a></td>
        <td>Baseline 2024</td>
        <td>The same-document half of the guard &mdash; intercepts SPA route changes for the route-leave confirm. The two primitives present as one guard (harvested as the navigation-guard intent, #129).</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Background_Fetch_API">Background Fetch API</a></td>
        <td>Limited availability</td>
        <td>The opt-in <code>durability: reload</code> tier &mdash; work that survives a full reload/close. Delegated to a service-worker adapter, NOT baked into the baseline (the intent borrows the vocabulary &ldquo;without requiring a service worker&rdquo;).</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/status_role"><code>role="status"</code></a></td>
        <td>WAI-ARIA</td>
        <td>Because the surface is off the current view, completion and failure are announced via a polite live region so a screen-reader user learns a backgrounded task finished without watching the rail.</td>
    </tr>
</table>

<h3>Task Lifecycle</h3>
<p>A task entry moves through the Background Task Intent's states:</p>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr><th>State</th><th>Description</th><th>Surface behavior</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>registered</code></td><td>Handed off (escalated async); now has an entry.</td><td>Entry appears in the rail.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>active</code></td><td>Work in progress.</td><td>Shows progress; arms the navigation guard.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>success</code></td><td>Resolved successfully.</td><td>Behaves per <code>persistence</code> (auto-clear if transient; may emit a toast).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>error</code></td><td>Failed.</td><td>Entry stays (sticky) and exposes retry via Reliability.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>dismissed</code></td><td>Removed by the user or by auto-clear.</td><td>Entry leaves the rail.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Dimensions (offered choices) vs. fixed mechanics</h3>
<p>
    A fork is exposed as a configurable dimension only when both branches are legitimate end-states for
    different products. The registration mechanism and surface resolution are fixed (variants would
    fragment interop); the rest are dimensions.
</p>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr><th>Axis</th><th>Values</th><th>Kind</th><th>Trait (non-default)</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>aggregation</strong></td><td><code>single</code> · <code>batch</code></td><td>Dimension (from intent)</td><td><code>withBatchAggregation</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>persistence</strong></td><td><code>transient</code> · <code>sticky</code></td><td>Dimension (from intent)</td><td><code>withStickyEntries</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>navigationGuard</strong></td><td><code>none</code> · <code>warn</code></td><td>Dimension (from intent)</td><td><code>withNavigationGuard</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>durability</strong></td><td><code>route</code> · <code>reload</code></td><td>Dimension (block-added) &mdash; <strong>future #134</strong>, not in the shipped baseline</td><td><code>withReloadDurability</code> (future)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><em>registration</em></td><td>bubbling <code>background-task-register</code> event</td><td><strong>Fixed mechanic</strong></td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
        <tr><td><em>surface resolution</em></td><td>nearest-ancestor, global-by-default</td><td><strong>Fixed mechanic</strong></td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Registration handoff</h3>
<p>
    A Loader crossing <code>escalation: async</code> dispatches a bubbling registration event; the nearest
    ancestor <code>&lt;background-tasks&gt;</code> surface adopts the carried Loader-state handle and renders
    its entry. The surface subscribes to a live handle &mdash; it does not re-implement progress.
</p>
{% set backgroundTasksHtml %}
<!-- Placed once in the app shell (a Layout rail) -->
<background-tasks aggregation="batch" persistence="sticky" navigation-guard></background-tasks>
{% endset %}
{{ autoToggle("background-tasks-surface", backgroundTasksHtml) }}
{% highlight "typescript" %}
// A Loader hands a still-running task off when it crosses the async threshold.
el.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('background-task-register', {
  bubbles: true,
  detail: {
    id: 'upload-42',
    label: 'Uploading photos',     // sentence case, -ing verb, <= 3 words (Loader label conventions)
    progress: 'determinate',
    loaderState,                    // the live Loader state machine, subscribed off-view
  },
}));
{% endhighlight %}

<h3>Events</h3>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr><th>Event</th><th>Direction</th><th>Detail</th><th>Cancelable</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>background-task-register</code></td><td>In (handoff)</td><td><code>{ id, label, progress, loaderState }</code></td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>background-task-state-change</code></td><td>Out</td><td><code>{ id, from, to }</code></td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>background-task-retry</code></td><td>Out (user)</td><td><code>{ id }</code></td><td>Yes</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>background-task-dismiss</code></td><td>Out (user / auto)</td><td><code>{ id, reason }</code></td><td>Yes</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Interface</h3>
<p>
    This is the shipped <strong>route-only baseline</strong> (#135). The reload-durability axis
    (<code>durability</code> / <code>withReloadDurability</code>) is a documented <strong>future</strong>
    tier (#134), not part of this config &mdash; see the dimensions table above.
</p>
<pre><code class="language-typescript">type BackgroundTaskState = 'registered' | 'active' | 'success' | 'error' | 'dismissed';
type ProgressMode = 'determinate' | 'indeterminate';

// A single observation of the backgrounded Loader's state (subscribed off-view).
interface LoaderSnapshot {
    state: 'active' | 'success' | 'error';
    progress?: number;                  // 0..1 fraction; only meaningful when determinate
    error?: Error;                      // present on 'error'
}

// Resolved surface behavior — set from defaults, flipped by traits (route-only baseline).
interface BackgroundTasksConfig {
    aggregation: 'single' | 'batch';     // default 'single'
    persistence: 'transient' | 'sticky'; // default 'transient' (errors are always sticky)
    navigationGuard: boolean;            // default false — arm beforeunload + route-leave guard
    completionToast: boolean;            // default false — emit a Feedback toast on completion
    retry: boolean;                      // default false — expose a per-task retry affordance
}</code></pre>

<h3>Exports</h3>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr><th>Export</th><th>Kind</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>BackgroundTasksElement</code></td><td>Class</td><td>The surface custom element (a Layout rail)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>withBatchAggregation</code></td><td>Trait</td><td>Many concurrent tasks, each with its own progress + retry</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>withStickyEntries</code></td><td>Trait</td><td>Resolved entries stay until dismissed</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>withNavigationGuard</code></td><td>Trait</td><td>Arm beforeunload + route-leave confirm while a task is active</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>withCompletionToast</code></td><td>Trait</td><td>Emit a Feedback toast on completion</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>withPerTaskRetry</code></td><td>Trait</td><td>Retry affordance delegating to Reliability</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>withReloadDurability</code></td><td>Trait <em>(future)</em></td><td><strong>Not shipped</strong> &mdash; the reload-durable tier (Background Fetch adapter) lands with #134</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>BackgroundTaskRegisterDetail</code> · <code>…StateChangeDetail</code> · <code>…RetryDetail</code> · <code>…DismissDetail</code></td><td>Detail types</td><td>The <code>detail</code> shape of each lifecycle event (see Events above)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>BackgroundTasksConfig</code></td><td>Interface</td><td>Resolved surface config (with <code>DEFAULT_CONFIG</code>)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>LoaderSnapshot</code> · <code>LoaderStateHandle</code></td><td>Interfaces</td><td>The carried live Loader-state handle and its snapshots</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>registerBackgroundTasks</code></td><td>Function</td><td>Registers the element with its default name</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
